      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis CFD benchmark studies",
      "description": "This evidence node consolidates findings from multiple independent published studies (Jones et al. 2019, Arvand & Graefe 2005, Taskin et al. 2012, Fraser et al. 2011) that characterized hemolysis prediction accuracy for rotary blood pumps using power-law damage models. The synthesis establishes that RANS-based CFD with Lagrangian particle tracking achieves NIH prediction errors below 15% relative to in-vitro measurements across a range of pump geometries and operating regimes, providing the empirical basis for the acceptance threshold used in this COU. The consolidation was performed by the Morrison lab computational team as part of a systematic evidence review conducted in 2023 prior to submission."
